                <note rend="inline" type="source">561.311D1/64: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Atherton</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-05-28T15:00:00+01:00"
                            >May 28, 1931—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 28—1:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>166. Department’s 147, May 26, 2 p.m. For the Department of Agriculture from
                    Olsen.</p>
                <p>“Countries represented Conference not recognizing fundamentals in solution wheat
                    problem. Since clearing house would have creation participating nations believe
                    it promising vehicle to obtain additional data such as port unloads, stocks
                    requirements, also improve statistical economic services participating nations
                    and influence production marketing policies exporting countries. No assurance
                    can induce Russia supply additional statistics but clearly may uncover
                    additional Russian information. Institute Agriculture not functioning
                    adequately. Clearing house may stimulate reforms. Our foreign services can
                    secure much valuable data but not in as strategic position as clearing house to
                    influence activities other nations. Great effort at Conference to place American
                    delegation in negative position. Clearing house purely informational and
                    educational and believe our participating desirable.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Atherton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
